rComments: I like how organized her lectures are and how she goes at a slow pace to make sure the class understands the concept first before moving on. Her tests reflect the practice questions and tutorial assignments that we did/were assigned. I appreciate how she remakes her own slides in a sense. Her final was very long though sadly.

The midterm was fine but the final is heavy, not only questions are difficult but also there are lots of questions need to answer. Although there are 3 hours for writing, only 5% of people leave early. Hope you could imagine the difficulty of the test.

Pretends she doesn't care about her students but actually cares. Goes over material slowly and step by step so that all students can follow along and makes the test really reasonable reflecting textbook, tutorial and lecture questions.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria']
